==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nonrepresentative
<hw>nonrepresentative</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not standing
for something else. Opposite of <ant>representative</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unsymbolic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not giving a true representation of the
characteristics of a group; -- of a sample or subgroup of a group;
<as>as, the weather we had in the summer of 1996 gave a
<ex>nonrepresentative</ex> view of our normal weather</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> biased, unrepresentative.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonresemblance</ent>⟦br⟧
